{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_21","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/zsh -lc 'nl -ba docs/changelog/changelog-2026-06-07.md'","aggregated_output":"     1\t# Changelog 2026-06-07\n     2\t\n     3\t## deepMerge\n     4\t\n     5\t- Implemented `deepMerge(target, source)` as an in-place merge that returns `target`, matching the task wording.\n     6\t- Recursively merges only plain object values; arrays, `null`, dates, and primitive values from `source` replace the target value.\n     7\t- Skips prototype-polluting keys to avoid unsafe side effects while merging untrusted object data.\n     8\t- Added regression coverage for nested merges, replacement values, non-object inputs, and unsafe keys because the visible flat-object test did not cover the full contract.\n     9\t- Tightened top-level inputs to plain objects and included enumerable symbol keys because deep object merge should not treat arrays or built-ins as merge containers, but should preserve all own enumerable object properties.\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
